This paper discusses discrimination prevention and privacy protection in data mining and publishing. It involves techniques for cleaning training datasets and outsourced datasets to prevent direct and indirect discriminatory decision rules. It also explores the relationship between privacy preserving data mining and discrimination prevention in data mining. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
